	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			REPRIEVE!<BR>
Hello all interested Paladins,<BR>
I have completed two pieces of The Armor of Ro quest! The Breastplate of Ro, and the Greaves of Ro, are now mine! *does a little dance* And I bring you good news, and bad news, and some clarification on some REALLY erroneous posts about the Armor of Ro. <BR>
<BR>
First the good news; if you have your basics covered (been a good paladin and have made plenty of friends, got your masters in smithing, and got your faction appropriate) this quest isn't nearly as hard as it appears (although it is time consuming).<BR>
<BR>
Now, the bad news: a 50th level anything (except maybe a druid) could no solo this quest throught it's entirety (the MM cauldrons being the hardest part). So if you have a solo mentality, might as well give up now. However, a group of low 30's (POSSIBLY high 20's if they were really good) could do everything this quest asks for. <BR>
<BR>
Now for clarification on some seriously erroneous posts. First off, you do NOT need amiable or better faction to get the molds....indifferent faction will suffice. I was indifferent to both Elisabeth and Thomas, and received the molds and information I needed. With near opposing races, you will have apprenhensive faction, and THAT you will need to correct (alot of human pallies have apprehensive faction with the dwarves). You DO need amiable or better faction for the Temple of Solusek Ro (where you gain the Sol Cauldron to mix the Ronium). The best way to gain faction the fastest is NOT killing shadowmen, but taking derv rings (4 at a time) to the named orc in South Ro, and/or 30 GP to the named wizard in South Ro (they are in the same place, by a hut, in the north west part of the zone). This took me about 2 hours to accomplish the faction I needed (you can con the named orc to see if you have amiable faction with the temple). You have to mix both the Ronium AND forge the armor itself. The Ronium is not smith required I don't believe and is not NO DROP so someone can make this for you. However, the molds are NO DROP and while forging the armor was trivial at 102 smithing skill, I would not dare to try this at less skill for fear of failing to make it. To forge the armor, take the mold and Ronium to any forge, and combine them (NO WATER, just the mold and ronium will suffice). Finally, the Armor of Ro is not NO DROP, so you can wear it, sell it, drop it on the ground, whatever you like.<BR>
<BR>
The stats for the BP are as follows:<BR>
<BR>
20 AC +4 STR +10 Fire saves 5.0 weight with a steel look.<BR>
<BR>
The stats for the Greaves of Ro are:<BR>
<BR>
14 AC +6 Stamina +10 Cold 3.7 weight and steel look. <BR>
<BR>
This is how I accomplished the quest for these parts:<BR>
<BR>
For the greaves I needed a Nightfall Giants head. These are not that rare, and are not NO DROP so you can purchase them (50-200 PP I've seen for them). One of my guild's wizards gave it to me after practicing his Ice Comet spell in WC for awhile hehe. <BR>
<BR>
The materials for the Ronium:<BR>
<BR>
The melatite you can purchase (up to 1000PP I've seen it sold for). My group has been camping Solusek's Eye, an we gained it off a CWG model MA gnomebot (rare drop). It is my understanding that any of the gnomes/bots can drop it, just most common off the MC and MA models.<BR>
<BR>
The Soil of Underfoot is gained from the priestess Ghalea at Kaladim Clerics Guild, and you will need amiable or better faction and 4 faerie (not pixie) dust. The soil is NO DROP and LORE so you will return here after each piece of Ro you make (joy).<BR>
<BR>
Sands of Ro are an uncommon drop off of the Sand Giants of Southern Ro and Oasis. It is neither NO DROP nor LORE and you can usually get it for free from any SG killing group or purchase it (I purchased one for 50 PP).<BR>
<BR>
2 Bars of Enchanted Platinum you can buy from any alloy selling store and have enchanted by a high level enchanter. I don't know the price as it was given to me as a gift. 200PP per bar I believe though.<BR>
<BR>
MistMoore Granite is garnered off any of the gargoyles in MistMoore (most commonly dropped by the Flouting and Leering). This is drop is not THAT rare, as my party gained 9 pieces in a 4 hour camp. You will need a high level puller (druid pref) for this, or a tight low 30's party to camp inside the castle.<BR>
<BR>
Breastplate of RO item:<BR>
<BR>
Two Dark Cauldrons off the Ancille Cooks in MistMoore are needed for this. They sit right smack dab in the middle of the castle, so good luck (again low 30's party, camping and pulling from the correct room in MM should be able to accomplish this). I had a 50th ranger from my Guild (Jeygo you're the best!) and a 33 Paladin camping with me for this, and it was HAIRY! (WTB clean shorts). In a 4 hour span, we gained 5 cauldrons (uncommon drop). <BR>
<BR>
Boots of Ro:<BR>
<BR>
Needed are the Kilij plans off the unamed Sand Giant in Southern Ro. The only way to tell the difference is by conning it (conned black to me at 28th level). My group camped for it for 4 hours with no luck one night. Next night, while upping faction for Temple of Solusek, I ran right into it as it was beating up on a 31st level ranger. Between both of us we killed it (low 20's party could take this one no sweat). It doesn't have the HP or Damage that a full SG has  The Kilij plans are LORE but not NO DROP.<BR>
<BR>
Well that's one I've accomplished so far. Good luck to the rest of yas, and gimme a holler ifn ya needs help <BR>
<BR>
Kruunch Spiritslammer (Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim)<BR>
&lt;28th Order - Legion of Heroes&gt;<BR>
Master Merchant &amp; Smithy<BR>
Veteran Brewer &amp; Tailor<BR>
Follower of Brell<BR>
Forger of Ro<BR>

			</font>
	
