		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			To obtain the armor of ro you need no smithing skill. It was soon changed after all the paladins were complaining that they were the only class that needed a trade skill to make there armor.<BR>
<BR>
All pieces of armor require one mold of the desired piece, and one bar of Ronium (no water).<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
BP of RO:<BR>
You will need 2 dark couldrins from the cooks in MM castle. i would sugest getting your 7 pieces of granate while your deep getting the couldrins. You trade the 2 couldrins to the High Elf paladin in rathe mountains for a mold.<BR>
<BR>
Grieves or RO:<BR>
The grieves of ro require one nightfall giant head. This giant spawns at nightfall in WC, wandering around the druid ring usually, and is there till it is killed or till day time. You turn this in for the Grieves mold.<BR>
<BR>
Boots of RO:<BR>
The boots of ro require the plans for the Braizen Brass Kilji, a rather nice weapon if you use the plans to obtain the sword instead of the boots, that is one of the reasons this part is more difficult. The giant that drops the plans is killed by the merchants in SRO, and some of the high level twinkers want the sword for there twinks, this is one of the more interesting parts to get. You turn the plans to the dwarf paladin for the Boots mold.<BR>
<BR>
Helm of RO:<BR>
The helm of ro is obtained by killing the undead cyclopses in SK, as far as i have seen these cyclopses spawn at night and stay till killed, however they mey poof at day break. you will need two of the skulld which you turn in for the Helm mold.<BR>
<BR>
Gauntlets of RO:<BR>
The locket off the sentry in SK is needed for the gauntlets, i dont remember the name, sory, but he spawns randomly anytime, when night falls however the becomes a wearwolf. I have only killed him in human form but i bleieve that if you kill him in wearwolf form you dont get the faction hits. you turn the locket in for the gauntlet mold.<BR>
<BR>
Bracers of RO:<BR>
These are obtained by getting 2 nets off the net master goblins in Lake rathe. They basicly swim in a big circle around the lake. However currently they DWK faction needed to get the mold from David is still broken, try haveing an enchanter turn in the stuff for the mold and makeing the bracer, or wolf form. I used wolf form and it worked fine for me, but some of my friends told me it didnt work for them. You turn in the 2 nets to david for the bracer mold.<BR>
<BR>
Vambraces of RO:<BR>
You need 2 rottin portions from the plauge sharks in eruds crossing. This is the only piece i have yet to get so i really cant give to much info on how to find the sharks. Any information you have wold be appriciated. You turn in the 2 portions for the Vambraces mold.<BR>
<BR>
As i stated before, all you put into the forge is one mold and one bar of ronium. <BR>
<BR>
Have fun, and i hope this helps some.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
									
